==Other projects==
In 2003 Burrow released a book entitled ''Taj Burrow's Book of Hot Surfing'',<ref name=book>[https://books.google.com/books/about/Taj_Burrow_s_Book_of_Hot_Surfing.html?id=ExrpkWI9HpsC ''Taj Burrow's Book of Hot Surfing'']</ref> and has also produced a series of his own [[surf film|surf videos]]: ''Sabotaj'' (2000),<ref name=sabotaj>[http://www.obsurfshop.com/video.php?id=270 ''Sabotaj'']</ref> ''Montaj'' (2002)<ref name=montaj>[http://www.obsurfshop.com/video.php?id=328 ''Montaj'']</ref> and ''Taj Burrow's Fair Bits'' (2005).<ref name=billabong />

In 2008–09 [[Globe International|Globe]] released a shoe line named after Burrow.<ref>[http://surfeurope.mpora.com/news/taj-resigns-with-globe-shoes/ 23-Jan-2009 Surf Europe article 'Taj re-signs with Globe Shoes', retrieved 24-Oct-2011]</ref>

Since 2005 Burrow has hosted the 'Taj Small Fries' junior surfing competition at [[Yallingup, Western Australia|Yallingup]], [[Western Australia]].<ref name=smallfries>{{cite web|title=Taj’s Small Fries grommet event set to roll in Yallingup|url=http://www.surfersvillage.com/surfing-news/44873|work=Surfers Village|accessdate=24 September 2013|author=Simon Barratt|date=January 2010}}</ref>

